00:40:07,471 --> 00:40:11,475
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.
SO YOU TELL ME EVERYTHING
THAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT.

677
00:40:11,475 --> 00:40:15,980
- I TOLD IT A THOUSAND TIMES.
- I DIDN'T HEAR IT THAT TIME.
  TELL ME AGAIN.

678
00:40:17,982 --> 00:40:20,985
WE SPENT MOST OF THE DAY
ON THE BOAT.  WE LEFT,
WE WERE GOIN' DOWNTOWN--

679
00:40:20,985 --> 00:40:23,487
BOAT ?
WHAT BOAT ?

680
00:40:23,487 --> 00:40:26,991
IT'S MY DAD'S BOAT.
 IT'S MORE LIKE A YACHT.

681
00:40:26,991 --> 00:40:29,994
HE NEVER USES IT.
HE'S AFRAID OF THE WATER.
IT MAKES HIM SEASICK.

682
00:40:30,494 --> 00:40:31,996
IT'S THE ONLY PLACE
HE NEVER LOOKS FOR
ME AND ELISE.

683
00:40:32,496 --> 00:40:35,499
LET ME BE CLEAR.
YOU TWO WERE SNAKIN' AROUND
BEHIND HIS BACK.

684
00:40:35,499 --> 00:40:37,501
THEY DIDN'T HAVE
A CHOICE.

685
00:40:37,501 --> 00:40:40,504
